<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 12:45PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Heavy Snow through Mid Afternoon...
A band of heavy snow will continue moving slowly eastward across
the Schoharie Valley, Capital District and Glens Falls Saratoga
region through mid this afternoon, before tapering off to lighter
snow later this afternoon. Snowfall rates of 1 to 2 inches per
hour within the heavy snow band, will lead to snow covered roads
and poor visibility. This includes the New York State Thruway in
the Capital District and the Northward from the Capital District
northward. Avoid unnecessary travel if possible, as conditions
will be hazardous.</description>
